#. Tag: title
#: smt_certificates.xml:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "Server Certificates"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:11
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For communication between the &smt; server and client machines, the "
"encrypted HTTPS protocol is used, requiring a server certificate. If the "
"certificate is not available, or if clients are not configured to use the "
"certificate, the communication between server and clients will fail."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:18
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Every client must be able to verify the server certificate by trusting the "
"CA (certificate authority) certificate that signed the server certificate. "
"Therefore, the &smt; server provides a copy of the CA at <filename>/srv/www/"
"htdocs/smt.crt</filename>. This CA can be downloaded from every client via "
"the URL <literal>http://<replaceable>FQDN</replaceable>/smt.crt</literal>. "
"The copy is created when &yast; writes the &smt; configuration. Whenever "
"&smt; is started with <command>systemctl start smt.target</command>, it "
"checks the certificate. If a new CA certificate exists, it is copied again. "
"Therefore, whenever the CA certificate is changed, restart &smt; using the "
"<command>systemctl restart smt.target</command> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:31
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the &smt; Server module applies configuration changes, it checks for "
"the existence of the common server certificate. If the certificate does not "
"exist, &yast; asks whether the certificate should be created. If the user "
"confirms, the &yast; CA Management module is started."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_certificates.xml:39
#, no-c-format
msgid "Certificate Expiration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:40
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The common server certificate &smt; uses is valid for one year. After that "
"time, a new certificate is needed. Either generate a new certificate using "
"&yast; CA Management module or import a new certificate using the &yast; "
"Common Server Certificate module. Both options are described in the "
"following sections."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:47
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As long as the same CA certificate is used, there is no need to update "
"certificates on the client machines. The generated CA certificate is valid "
"for 10 years."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_certificates.xml:53
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a New Common Server Certificate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:54
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create a new common server certificate with &yast;, proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:60
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Start &yast; and select <menuchoice> <guimenu>Security and Users</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>CA Management</guimenu> </menuchoice>. Alternatively, start the "
"&yast; CA Management module from a command line by entering <command>yast2 "
"ca_mgm</command> as &rootuser;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:68
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select the required CA and click <guimenu>Enter CA</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enter the password if entering a CA for the first time. &yast; displays the "
"CA key information in the <guimenu>Description</guimenu> tab."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:79
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click the <guimenu>Certificates</guimenu> tab (see <xref linkend=\"fig.yast."
"ca_cert\"/>) and select <menuchoice> <guimenu>Add</guimenu> <guimenu>Add "
"Server Certificate</guimenu> </menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_certificates.xml:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "Certificates of a CA"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:98
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enter the fully qualified domain name of the server as <guimenu>Common Name</"
"guimenu>. Add a valid e-mail address of the server administrator. Other "
"fields, such as <guimenu>Organization</guimenu>, <guimenu>Organizational "
"Unit</guimenu>, <guimenu>Locality</guimenu>, and <guimenu>State</guimenu> "
"are optional. Click <guimenu>Next</guimenu> to proceed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_certificates.xml:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "Host Name in Server Certificate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The server certificate must contain the correct host name. If the client "
"requests server <literal>https://some.hostname/</literal>, then "
"<literal>some.hostname</literal> must be part of the certificate. The host "
"name must either be used as the <guimenu>Common Name</guimenu>, see <xref "
"linkend=\"step.new.cert1\"/>, or as the <guimenu>Subject Alternative Name</"
"guimenu>, see <xref linkend=\"step.new.cert2\"/>: <literal>DNS:some."
"hostname</literal> and <literal>IP:<replaceable>&lt;ipaddress&gt;</"
"replaceable></literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enter a <guimenu>Password</guimenu> for the private key of the certificate "
"and re-enter it in the next field to verify it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:125
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to define a <guimenu>Subject Alternative Name</guimenu>, click "
"<guimenu>Advanced Options</guimenu>, select <guimenu>Subject Alternative "
"Name</guimenu> from the list and click <guimenu>Add</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_certificates.xml:132
#, no-c-format
msgid "Subject Alternative Name"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:133
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If <guimenu>Subject Alternative Name</guimenu> is present in the server "
"certificate, then it needs to contain the DNS entry. If <guimenu>Subject "
"Alternative Name</guimenu> is present, the <guimenu>Common Name</guimenu> "
"(CN) is not checked anymore."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to keep the default values for the other options, like "
"<guimenu>Key Length</guimenu> and <guimenu>Valid Period</guimenu>, click "
"<guimenu>Next</guimenu>. An overview of the certificate to be created is "
"shown."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:149
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <guimenu>Create</guimenu> to generate the certificate."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:154
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To export the new certificate as the common server certificate, select it in "
"the <guimenu>Certificates</guimenu> tab and select <menuchoice> "
"<guimenu>Export</guimenu> <guimenu>Export as Common Server Certificate</"
"guimenu> </menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:162 smt_certificates.xml:217
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After having created a new certificate, restart &smt; using the "
"<command>systemctl restart smt.target</command> command. Restarting &smt; "
"ensures that the new certificate is copied from <filename>/etc/ssl/certs/"
"YaST-CA.pem</filename> to <filename>/srv/www/htdocs/smt.crt</filename>, the "
"copy &smt; uses. Restarting &smt; also restarts the Web server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For detailed information about managing certification and further usage of "
"the &yast; CA Management module and the Common Server Certificate module, "
"refer to the &secguide; coming with the base system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_certificates.xml:179
#, no-c-format
msgid "Importing a Common Server Certificate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:180
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can import an own common server certificate from a file. The certificate "
"to be imported needs to be in the PKCS12 format with CA chain. Common server "
"certificates can be imported with the &yast; Common Server Certificate "
"module."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:186
#, no-c-format
msgid "To import an own certificate with &yast;, proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:191
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Start &yast; and select <menuchoice> <guimenu>Security and Users</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Common Server Certificate</guimenu> </menuchoice>. Alternatively, "
"start the &yast; Common Server Certificate module from the command line by "
"entering <command>yast2 common_cert</command> as &rootuser;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:198
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The description of the currently used common server certificate is shown in "
"the dialog that opens."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:204
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click <guimenu>Import</guimenu> and select the file containing the "
"certificate to be imported. Specify the certificate password in the "
"<guimenu>Password</guimenu> field."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:211
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Press <guimenu>Next</guimenu>. If the certificate is successfully imported, "
"close &yast; with <guimenu>Finish</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_certificates.xml:230
#, no-c-format
msgid "Synchronizing Time between &smt; Server and Clients"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:231
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The synchronization of time between the &smt; server and clients is highly "
"recommended. Each server certificate has a validity period. If the client "
"happens to be set to a time outside of this period, the certificate "
"validation on the client side fails."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_certificates.xml:237
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Therefore, it is advisable to keep the time on the server and clients "
"synchronized. You can easily synchronize the time using NTP (network time "
"protocol). Use <command>yast2 ntp-client</command> to configure an NTP "
"client. Find detailed information about NTP in the &admin;."
msgstr ""
